						               													<description>Liberators! Books and Miniatures allow you to recreate the Wars of South American Independence on your game table.  Liberators! Books give you all the information you need to learn about and game this fascinating period.  The books include the history of the conflict; organization, tactics and uniforms of the armies and scenarios to play including map and order of battle information. Liberators! Miniatures are a museum quality range of &amp;quot;heroic&amp;quot; scale 15mm figures that allow you to build the armies listed in the scenarios...or to create scenarios of your own!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game features:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Players take the role of a brigade or division commander in the South America Independence War in the XIX Century.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Take your side as Liberators Armies of the North &amp;ldquo;Simon Bolivar&amp;rdquo; or South &amp;ldquo;San Martin&amp;rdquo; Against the Royalist Spanish Army Forces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Build your armies with information on military uniformology, the colors pattern and symbols of the XIX Century independence Era; like Gran Colombian Army, Llanero/Peasant infantry, Argentine Grenadiers, Royalist/Spanish Infantry or even Irish/British legion forces involved in the conflict. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The game is tactical in nature, focusing on the movement of individual battalions and regiments of cavalry and use of artillery units. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The game is designed to cover different periods of time, divided into several volumes, including data on the theaters of operations involved in every war and the organization of the armies involved. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Numerous scenarios each side and ready to be played&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
